    "problem_statement": "You run a two-factory manufacturing pipeline. Factory A makes components, then Factory B finishes the same jobs.\nEach factory is its own job shop with one-job-per-machine exclusivity and no preemption.\nEvery job must finish all of its Factory A operations before that same job may start any Factory B operation.\nYour objective is to minimize the coupled makespan: the time when the final Factory B operation finishes.\n\nInstance size: 6 jobs, 7 machines in each factory.\nJobs and ordered operations:\n- Job 1: Factory A MA3 (7) -> MA2 (2) -> MA4 (4) -> MA1 (2) -> MA5 (9) -> MA7 (7) -> MA6 (1); Factory B MB5 (2) -> MB1 (4) -> MB7 (1) -> MB2 (7) -> MB6 (1) -> MB3 (4) -> MB4 (1)\n- Job 2: Factory A MA5 (2) -> MA2 (9) -> MA3 (2) -> MA4 (1) -> MA1 (4) -> MA7 (8) -> MA6 (9); Factory B MB5 (7) -> MB6 (6) -> MB2 (8) -> MB1 (8) -> MB3 (6) -> MB4 (5) -> MB7 (4)\n- Job 3: Factory A MA7 (9) -> MA2 (7) -> MA6 (3) -> MA1 (6) -> MA3 (3) -> MA5 (8) -> MA4 (7); Factory B MB3 (1) -> MB6 (2) -> MB4 (9) -> MB7 (6) -> MB5 (6) -> MB1 (6) -> MB2 (8)\n- Job 4: Factory A MA5 (1) -> MA4 (8) -> MA1 (6) -> MA7 (3) -> MA2 (2) -> MA3 (8) -> MA6 (1); Factory B MB1 (4) -> MB6 (5) -> MB3 (3) -> MB4 (4) -> MB2 (7) -> MB5 (7) -> MB7 (8)\n- Job 5: Factory A MA1 (7) -> MA2 (4) -> MA4 (3) -> MA5 (2) -> MA3 (3) -> MA6 (3) -> MA7 (4); Factory B MB7 (4) -> MB4 (1) -> MB5 (8) -> MB3 (3) -> MB6 (5) -> MB2 (5) -> MB1 (1)\n- Job 6: Factory A MA2 (7) -> MA4 (7) -> MA5 (2) -> MA3 (8) -> MA6 (7) -> MA7 (1) -> MA1 (4); Factory B MB6 (2) -> MB5 (4) -> MB7 (8) -> MB1 (3) -> MB2 (2) -> MB3 (6) -> MB4 (1)\n\nConstraints:\n- A machine handles at most one job at a time.\n- Each job must respect its listed operation order inside each factory.\n- Factory B job Jx cannot start until Factory A job Jx has fully completed.\n- When you emit a schedule, every required operation must appear exactly once.\n\nA deterministic feasible baseline schedule is provided below. If you stop immediately or fail to p